subSection.paragraph:
Compound multilocular disc-pores
(
Figs 1
C-F, M-P), each has a central loculus, a ring of subcentral loculi, and another concentric ring of peripheral loculi. Pores with indistinct peripheral loculi and each with 3–5 subcentral loculi (
Figs 1C and F
) present on adult female, third-instar male nymph (pre-pupa) and male pupa. Pores with distinct peripheral loculi present on adult female, first-instar nymph and cysts: pores each with 5–8 subcentral loculi (
Figs 1D and E
) present around spiracles in adult female; pores each with 3–6 subcentral loculi (
Figs 1M and N
) present near each spiracle on first-instar nymph; pores each with 3–8 subcentral loculi (
Fig. 1O
) present on cysts but these pores between antennae sometimes small and lacking part or all of peripheral loculi (
Fig. 1P
).

